# Guesses
Aqui são dados os primeiros chutes.

```r
guesses_30_01_2023 <- tibble::tribble(
  ~Country, ~Distance, ~Direction,
  "Malta", 8819, "West",
  "Jamaica", 383, "North",
  "Bahamas", 393, "South"
)
```

# Limite dos países
Baixando os limites dos países.

```r
data(countries110, package = "rnaturalearth")
```

Convertendo pro formato `sf`.

```r
countries <- countries110 %>% 
  st_as_sf() %>% 
  st_transform(crs = 4326) #4326 = WGS84, 4674 = SIRGAS2000
```

Unificando a variável `chutes` com o limite dos países.
Não existe o país `Malta`.

```r
starting <- countries %>% 
  # dplyr::select(SUBUNIT) %>% 
  dplyr::select(BRK_NAME) %>%
  # filter(
  #   BRK_NAME == "Malta"
  # ) %>% 
  inner_join(
    guesses_30_01_2023, by = c("BRK_NAME" = "Country")
  ) 
# %>% 
#   mutate(
#     color = RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(
#       # n(),
#       3,
#       "Set1")
#   )
```

Encontrar o centróide de cada país*. 
* Não se aplica ao `USA`.

```r
centers <- starting %>% 
  st_make_valid() %>% 
  st_centroid()
```

```
## Warning in st_centroid.sf(.): st_centroid assumes attributes are constant over
## geometries of x
```


```r
centers
```

# Visualização do mapa

```r
(test <- leaflet() %>% 
   addTiles() %>% 
   addPolygons(
     data = starting,
     # fillColor = ~color,
     stroke = FALSE,
     opacity = 1,
   ) %>% 
   addMarkers(
     data = centers
   )
 )
```

# Gerando o raio

```r
circles <- centers %>% 
  st_buffer(
    dist = centers$Distance*1000
  ) %>% 
  st_cast(
    "LINESTRING"
  )
```

```
## Warning in st_cast.sf(., "LINESTRING"): repeating attributes for all
## sub-geometries for which they may not be constant
```

# Mapa+Raio

```r
leaflet() %>% 
  addTiles() %>% 
  addPolylines(
    data = circles,
    # color = ~color,
    popup = ~BRK_NAME
  ) %>% 
  addMarkers(
    data = centers
  )
```

# Interseção

```r
overlaps <- circles %>% 
  st_intersection() %>% 
  filter(
    n.overlaps >= 1
  )
```

```
## although coordinates are longitude/latitude, st_intersection assumes that they
## are planar
```

# Zoom na área

```r
leaflet() %>% 
  addTiles() %>% 
  addCircles(
    data = overlaps
  ) %>% 
  # 100km search area
  addPolylines(
    data = overlaps %>% st_buffer(dist = 100*1000)
  )
```
